WEBVTT

00:14.531 --> 00:22.332
♪♪

00:22.367 --> 00:25.611
-There are all sorts of ways
to hit a cue ball.

00:28.718 --> 00:30.237
The thing you're trying to do

00:30.271 --> 00:32.170
is send it
in a particular direction,

00:32.204 --> 00:36.070
to hit another ball and drop
that ball into a pocket,

00:36.105 --> 00:39.591
but it's where you send
the cue ball next

00:39.625 --> 00:43.353
that separates you
from the others.

00:43.388 --> 00:44.975
When you first start playing,

00:45.010 --> 00:47.392
you think it's only
about that one ball.

00:47.426 --> 00:51.913
You can put backspins,
sidespin or topspin on a ball,

00:51.948 --> 00:55.365
or you can make it stop
on a dime, bounce off a rail.

00:55.400 --> 01:00.094
You can hit a ball soft, hard,
or just give it a little kiss.

01:00.129 --> 01:01.820
You can send a ball
behind another ball

01:01.854 --> 01:04.961
to make it hard for
your opponent to make a shot.

01:04.995 --> 01:09.034
Once you have the skills,
you can do any of these things.

01:11.416 --> 01:16.490
♪♪

01:16.524 --> 01:21.426
♪♪

01:21.460 --> 01:26.224
Some dads take their kids
to church or to the ball game.

01:26.258 --> 01:28.157
That's what some dads do.

01:28.191 --> 01:35.957
♪♪

01:35.992 --> 01:38.581
My dad?
He took me to pool halls,

01:38.615 --> 01:43.482
and he taught me how to play
a game called 9-ball.

01:43.517 --> 01:44.966
-Are you ready?
-Yeah.

01:45.001 --> 01:46.796
-Mm!
Alright, fellas.

01:46.830 --> 01:48.004
I tell you what.

01:48.038 --> 01:49.419
We'll put my watch
against your $50.

01:49.454 --> 01:51.835
It's worth three --
five times more than that.

01:51.870 --> 01:54.148
-Wait, hold on.
What are you doing?

01:54.183 --> 01:55.253
-What do you say?

01:55.287 --> 01:57.496
Me and my sentimental,
watch-loving son

01:57.531 --> 01:58.946
against you two fellows,

01:58.980 --> 02:00.430
and I tell you what
because we -- we are...

02:00.465 --> 02:02.501
-No, Dad. Dad, come on.
That's your grandpa's watch.

02:02.536 --> 02:04.227
-Zip it. Zip it.
-It costs...

02:07.196 --> 02:09.059
Sorry.

02:09.094 --> 02:13.167
Why don't you run and get me
a pack of cigarettes?

02:13.202 --> 02:14.824
That shirt really brings
out your eyes.

02:14.858 --> 02:16.653
-Here is to your grandpa.

02:20.174 --> 02:22.797
-Nice watch.

02:22.832 --> 02:25.973
-Nine-ball, succession pool --

02:26.007 --> 02:28.976
where you got to
knock them down in order.

02:29.010 --> 02:31.323
This is truly a sport.

02:31.358 --> 02:35.707
It takes skill,
and, more importantly...

02:35.741 --> 02:39.538
it takes foresight.

02:39.573 --> 02:41.540
-Ah, come on!

02:41.575 --> 02:44.819
-I love $50.

02:44.854 --> 02:47.891
Nine-ball -- sport of kings.

02:47.926 --> 02:49.410
What do you say, fellas?
Double or nothing?

02:49.445 --> 02:51.205
-Yeah, not this time.
-I don't think so.

02:51.240 --> 02:53.414
-Well, thank you so much
for your patronage.

02:56.279 --> 02:58.350
-Could have at least
saved me a shot.

02:58.385 --> 03:00.387
-Well, I tell you what,

03:00.421 --> 03:03.355
next game, you shoot first.

03:03.390 --> 03:05.012
Now, how about you get us
a couple drinks?

03:05.046 --> 03:06.738
My treat.

03:18.715 --> 03:22.236
[ Vehicle approaching ]

03:27.414 --> 03:29.933
Hey, kiddo, I didn't realize
how late it was.

03:29.968 --> 03:32.142
Your mom is gonna have my hide.
Let's skedaddle.

03:32.177 --> 03:33.558
-Come on, let's just stay
a little bit longer?

03:33.592 --> 03:35.249
-I'll let you drive.

03:35.284 --> 03:36.733
-Awesome.

03:36.768 --> 03:42.532
♪♪

03:42.567 --> 03:45.466
-Chip?
[ Smooches ]

03:45.501 --> 03:46.605
-Yeah.

03:46.640 --> 03:48.089
[ Engine starts ]

03:50.575 --> 03:53.716
-Ah, damn it, go!
Go, Dallas!

03:53.750 --> 03:55.476
Aah!

03:55.511 --> 03:57.409
Jesus, easy, boy!

04:01.275 --> 04:02.794
-Dallas, I ain't
telling you again.

04:02.828 --> 04:04.830
Get up.

04:04.865 --> 04:06.280
You're not staying home
from school,

04:06.315 --> 04:08.420
so you get that out
of your head right now.

04:35.171 --> 04:38.588
Hey, I need your help cleaning
out the shed after dinner.

04:38.623 --> 04:41.419
-Can't.
-Is that so?

04:41.453 --> 04:45.354
-Dad has got a game
with some guys from Kentwood.

04:45.388 --> 04:48.011
-Forget it.
-He wants me there.

04:50.359 --> 04:51.843
Dad, tell her what
the deal is tonight.

04:51.877 --> 04:55.329
-You're not going,
and that's the end of it.

04:55.364 --> 04:57.124
-We'll see.

04:57.158 --> 05:00.230
-Yeah, we will see,
won't we?

05:03.717 --> 05:06.306
[ Door closes ]

05:10.758 --> 05:12.484
Did you even hear that?

05:14.590 --> 05:16.108
Hey!

05:23.184 --> 05:27.016
[ Dishes clattering loudly ]

05:30.019 --> 05:31.814
That's trouble, you know.

05:31.848 --> 05:35.265
You never help me
discipline him.

05:35.300 --> 05:37.337
He is barely squeaking
by in school!

05:37.371 --> 05:39.062
-He's fine.

05:39.097 --> 05:40.167
-By your standards, maybe.

05:40.201 --> 05:42.859
Did it ever occur to you

05:42.894 --> 05:44.482
to be his parent
instead of his playmate?

05:44.516 --> 05:46.207
-[ Sighs ]

05:48.693 --> 05:50.591
Just one cup of coffee.

05:50.626 --> 05:52.731
He's doing fine.

05:52.766 --> 05:54.975
-What do you mean by that?

05:56.701 --> 05:58.737
-Well, what I mean is

05:58.772 --> 06:02.362
[chuckles]
he's doing fine, Gina.

06:04.778 --> 06:06.711
-I thought you'd had enough
of this shit when you was a kid.

06:06.745 --> 06:08.195
-Damn it, Gina, don't.

06:08.229 --> 06:11.405
I know the road you're going
down. Don't do it.

06:11.440 --> 06:15.236
-Shit!
I'm gonna be late again.

06:15.271 --> 06:17.066
We need to talk.
I mean it.

06:17.100 --> 06:19.896
-I'm not worried, Gina.

06:19.931 --> 06:24.176
[ Conversation continues ]

06:32.426 --> 06:37.983
♪♪

06:38.018 --> 06:43.782
♪♪

06:43.817 --> 06:45.439
-I can't just leave work
like that

06:45.474 --> 06:47.165
every time you cause
a problem at school.

06:47.199 --> 06:49.961
I'm gonna lose my job
over your little stunts!

06:49.995 --> 06:55.000
♪♪

06:55.035 --> 07:00.247
♪♪

07:00.281 --> 07:02.076
Oh, God.

07:02.111 --> 07:06.598
♪♪

07:06.633 --> 07:09.014
-Mom?
Mom, let me see.

07:09.049 --> 07:10.499
-Dallas.
-Mom, let me see!

07:10.533 --> 07:12.155
-Dallas!

07:17.367 --> 07:18.955
Honey...

07:20.957 --> 07:22.511
[ Door opens ]

07:22.545 --> 07:24.754
[ Door slams ]

07:24.789 --> 07:27.136
You know how your daddy can get!

07:31.968 --> 07:34.937
[ Cries ]

07:34.971 --> 07:37.974
[ Vehicle approaches ]

07:41.530 --> 07:42.979
-Your daddy around?

07:44.533 --> 07:46.880
-No.

07:46.914 --> 07:49.503
-He say when he'll be back?
-No.

07:49.538 --> 07:53.990
-[ Scoffs ] Well, why don't
that surprise me?

07:54.025 --> 07:57.615
Well, tell him Earl stopped by.

07:57.649 --> 07:59.375
He'll know why.

08:03.897 --> 08:06.037
[ Tires screech ]

08:10.455 --> 08:14.321
-I always thought I was gonna
have a big life --

08:14.355 --> 08:18.636
nice house,
two cars, three kids.

08:18.670 --> 08:20.361
Just like on the TV.

08:22.536 --> 08:24.538
This is it.
-Let's face it.

08:24.573 --> 08:26.816
He hasn't been good
to you in forever.

08:26.851 --> 08:29.750
-Only part of my dream
that come true is Dallas.

08:29.785 --> 08:31.821
You know how you know
when it's over, Sandy?

08:31.856 --> 08:33.167
They stop kissing you.

08:33.202 --> 08:36.169
-Better no man
than a worthless one.

08:36.205 --> 08:38.068
-Who you calling worthless,
Sandy?

08:38.102 --> 08:39.346
-Dallas.

08:39.380 --> 08:40.692
-I see the way
you flirt with him.

08:40.727 --> 08:42.176
-Oh, please.

08:42.211 --> 08:43.453
-And you -- you --
you wonder why he takes off!

08:43.488 --> 08:44.731
You're bad-mouthing him
all the time.

08:44.765 --> 08:45.939
-That is not fair!

08:45.973 --> 08:47.078
-It's true.
You drove him away!

08:47.112 --> 08:48.562
-Go to your room.
Go!

08:48.597 --> 08:51.841
I don't want to hear
another word out of you, go!

08:51.876 --> 08:53.222
Get!

08:55.880 --> 08:57.778
[ Door closes ]

08:57.813 --> 09:02.611
♪♪

09:02.645 --> 09:05.579
-[ Breathing heavily ]

09:05.614 --> 09:15.589
♪♪

09:15.624 --> 09:25.599
♪♪

09:25.634 --> 09:35.609
♪♪

09:35.644 --> 09:45.619
♪♪

09:45.654 --> 09:55.629
♪♪

09:55.664 --> 10:05.639
♪♪

10:05.674 --> 10:15.649
♪♪

10:15.684 --> 10:25.659
♪♪

10:25.694 --> 10:35.669
♪♪

10:35.704 --> 10:39.639
♪♪

10:39.673 --> 10:42.780
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:42.814 --> 10:52.790
♪♪

10:52.824 --> 10:57.139
♪♪

10:57.173 --> 11:00.142
-♪ Make you feel real good

11:00.176 --> 11:06.976
♪♪

11:07.011 --> 11:13.673
♪♪

11:13.707 --> 11:16.330
-Well, look at what
the cat drug in.

11:16.365 --> 11:17.918
-♪ I say "yeah"

11:17.953 --> 11:19.161
-She's a beaut.

11:19.195 --> 11:21.197
-Yeah.
You seen Cal around, Jackie?

11:21.232 --> 11:24.822
-Earlier.
You two aren't together?

11:24.856 --> 11:26.547
-Can I get a drink?

11:26.582 --> 11:29.723
♪♪

11:29.758 --> 11:33.037
[ Soda can opens ]

11:33.589 --> 11:34.901
-So if you're not
with your dad,

11:34.935 --> 11:36.212
how'd you get here anyway?

11:36.247 --> 11:39.560
-Yo, Dallas!
You're up.

11:39.595 --> 11:42.702
-Coming.
Be right back.

11:42.736 --> 11:44.704
-Good because I'm not done
with you yet.

11:44.738 --> 11:50.433
♪♪

11:50.468 --> 11:52.470
-Wait, you're Dallas?

11:52.504 --> 11:56.543
-Last time I checked, and, uh,
you must be Wayne.

11:56.577 --> 12:00.133
-No, kid.
No, this isn't Toys "R" Us.

12:00.167 --> 12:01.893
We're playing for money here.

12:03.792 --> 12:05.241
-Nine-ball, it's the bottom
of the break.

12:05.276 --> 12:07.209
Call your last shot.

12:07.243 --> 12:09.107
-Let's rack them.

12:09.142 --> 12:13.042
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:13.077 --> 12:23.052
♪♪

12:23.087 --> 12:26.884
♪♪

12:26.918 --> 12:28.264
-Oh.

12:28.299 --> 12:31.233
-Believe you just lost all that
paper-route money, kid.

12:31.267 --> 12:37.757
♪♪

12:37.791 --> 12:44.073
♪♪

12:44.108 --> 12:45.695
-Oh!

12:45.730 --> 12:48.595
-I -- I do believe this is
what they call "ball in hand."

12:48.629 --> 12:50.459
so, uh, let's see.

12:50.493 --> 12:55.636
If I were a cue ball,
where would I want to be?

12:55.671 --> 12:57.259
I don't know, Wayne.
What do you think?

12:57.293 --> 12:59.261
Because, you know, I got a lot
of different options here.

12:59.295 --> 13:01.953
You know, I could take a shot
on that side pocket right there.

13:01.988 --> 13:05.785
Maybe I could spice some things
up and try and do a bank.

13:05.819 --> 13:07.131
-Ooh!

13:07.165 --> 13:09.271
-I'm not gonna feel so bad
about whooping your narrow hide.

13:09.305 --> 13:11.273
-Well, uh, you want
to make it $40,

13:11.307 --> 13:14.172
so you can take me
a real good lesson?

13:14.207 --> 13:15.346
-Done.

13:15.380 --> 13:17.727
-Oh, my, the heat is on.

13:17.762 --> 13:19.177
Ahh.

13:19.212 --> 13:25.839
♪♪

13:25.874 --> 13:27.323
Excuse me.

13:27.358 --> 13:34.641
♪♪

13:34.675 --> 13:36.816
Nine-ball,
one rail, corner back here.

13:36.850 --> 13:38.369
-Never happen.

13:42.545 --> 13:45.479
-Oh!
-Oh!

13:45.514 --> 13:47.412
-Never is a long time.

13:47.447 --> 13:50.553
-Afraid not.
You didn't call a pocket.

13:50.588 --> 13:52.383
-Yes, I did.
I -- I pointed to the...

13:52.417 --> 13:55.696
-He didn't call it,
did he, Seth?

13:55.731 --> 13:58.872
Anybody else hear him call it?

13:58.907 --> 14:00.667
Seems like we all
on the same page.

14:00.701 --> 14:02.738
-You're a dick.
You know what I said.

14:02.772 --> 14:04.360
-Bar ain't no place
for a kid, nohow.

14:04.395 --> 14:08.192
-The boy called it right.

14:08.226 --> 14:09.779
-This old man talking to me?

14:09.814 --> 14:12.506
-Uh, no disrespect,
but I did hear him.

14:12.541 --> 14:14.025
-I don't see how this is
any of your concern.

14:14.060 --> 14:17.373
-Well, you asked everyone,
and I believe I qualify.

14:17.408 --> 14:20.031
-Consider yourself
disqualified.

14:20.066 --> 14:21.619
-Is that right?

14:21.653 --> 14:24.346
This boy beat you
fair and square.

14:24.380 --> 14:27.901
-Hey, boy, that's enough.

14:27.936 --> 14:30.352
-Jackie's right.

14:30.386 --> 14:32.699
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

14:32.733 --> 14:34.735
-Come on, get back.
Mnh-mnh.

14:39.154 --> 14:40.914
-Take your money, son.

14:40.949 --> 14:46.023
♪♪

14:46.057 --> 14:48.922
-Oh, damn it.

14:50.924 --> 14:52.581
[ Horn honks ]

15:01.970 --> 15:03.903
-What was that?

15:03.937 --> 15:06.940
-Why don't you just mind
your own business?

15:06.975 --> 15:08.908
-Yeah, okay.

15:08.942 --> 15:12.325
Uh, listen, why don't you just
tell me you live

15:12.359 --> 15:13.636
within a reasonable distance,

15:13.671 --> 15:15.431
and I'll take you home
to your mama?

15:15.466 --> 15:16.916
-I don't have a mama.

15:18.331 --> 15:21.610
I -- I mean --
I mean, she died.

15:21.644 --> 15:24.233
-So who -- who do you stay
with then, boy?

15:24.268 --> 15:27.650
-My dad, but, uh, you know,
he -- he had to go somewhere.

15:27.685 --> 15:29.135
You know, he left me
with a buddy of his.

15:29.169 --> 15:30.860
You know, he didn't realize
what a drunk the guy was.

15:30.895 --> 15:33.587
You know, he -- he beat the crap
out of me earlier.

15:33.622 --> 15:35.003
Can't go back there,
or he'll kill me.

15:35.037 --> 15:37.833
-Uh, is there anywhere
I can take you,

15:37.867 --> 15:39.766
or anyone
I can drop you off with?

15:39.800 --> 15:41.871
Or wh-what about a neighbor
or a...

15:41.906 --> 15:45.013
-My dad is at a pool hall
called Fatty's in Baton Rouge.

15:47.981 --> 15:50.466
You know, if you could just,
you know, drop me off there,

15:50.501 --> 15:52.641
everything would be cool.

16:08.208 --> 16:11.971
You know, my dad is actually
a professional pool player.

16:12.005 --> 16:14.559
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah, big time.

16:16.768 --> 16:18.218
-So wh-what's happening?

16:18.253 --> 16:20.151
Is he on a circuit or something?

16:22.671 --> 16:25.087
-Yeah, sort of.
-Hmm.

16:27.055 --> 16:29.816
Well, what you do mean
"sort of" or something?

16:29.850 --> 16:32.336
-I don't know.
He just, you know, plays around.

16:32.370 --> 16:33.854
-Yeah.

16:33.889 --> 16:38.480
Yeah, so basically he just plays
in bars for money, right?

16:38.514 --> 16:41.310
-Well, n-not just bars,
you know, tournaments, too.

16:41.345 --> 16:44.003
He's actually making a real
big name for himself.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.590
Yeah, I mean, you know,
people actually compare him

16:45.625 --> 16:47.661
to Willie Mosconi.

16:47.696 --> 16:51.872
-Ah, is that right now?
Heh, Willie Mosconi?

16:51.907 --> 16:53.943
-You'll see when you meet him.

17:03.194 --> 17:06.025
[ Train whistle blows ]

17:11.237 --> 17:14.032
-This is your last warning.
Get up.

17:15.931 --> 17:19.071
Dallas?

17:19.107 --> 17:20.901
Dallas?

17:24.112 --> 17:26.906
[ Horn blares ]

17:36.745 --> 17:38.057
-What time is it?

17:38.091 --> 17:39.817
-About 7:30.

17:39.851 --> 17:42.268
Come here.
Lie down here.

17:42.302 --> 17:43.786
Go lie down.

17:49.033 --> 17:51.656
-You know, uh, you should
show me some moves.

17:51.691 --> 17:55.108
-I-I don't think so.
-Why not?

17:55.143 --> 17:57.490
-I'm-a let you answer
that question.

17:57.524 --> 17:58.732
-How far away from Baton Rouge?

17:58.767 --> 18:02.253
-It's down the road that way.

18:02.288 --> 18:04.566
-Okay. Later.

18:04.600 --> 18:07.914
-Hey, wait, hold on!
-That's okay.

18:07.948 --> 18:09.847
Wouldn't want to end up
on Amber Alert.

18:09.881 --> 18:12.953
-You still might, smart-ass.

18:13.954 --> 18:16.785
Okay, fine.
Suit yourself.

18:16.819 --> 18:19.063
-I will!
-Have a nice walk.

18:20.685 --> 18:28.486
♪♪

18:28.521 --> 18:36.287
♪♪

18:36.322 --> 18:43.950
♪♪

18:43.984 --> 18:46.504
-I can't tell you how sorry
I am about your father.

18:46.539 --> 18:49.266
-Well, thank you for taking
care of everything, Merle.

18:49.300 --> 18:50.888
-You bet, Joe.

18:50.922 --> 18:52.614
He'd have done
the same thing for me.

18:52.648 --> 18:54.685
-Mm.

18:54.719 --> 18:58.275
-Now, what are my chances
on talking you

18:58.309 --> 19:01.450
into joining the 21st century
and buying a cellphone?

19:01.485 --> 19:02.658
-No, I'm...

19:02.693 --> 19:04.350
-I could have called you
a week ago.

19:04.384 --> 19:07.284
-Well, I'm just not gonna put a
microwave up against my ears.

19:07.318 --> 19:08.733
It's not gonna happen.

19:08.768 --> 19:11.529
-I'd settle for
a mailing address.

19:11.564 --> 19:12.806
Mm.

19:12.841 --> 19:14.981
Well, as executor
of your father's estate,

19:15.015 --> 19:17.811
and I use that term loosely,
I need your signature

19:17.846 --> 19:19.917
on a couple of things
to finalize his will.

19:19.951 --> 19:22.402
His years in assisted living
pretty much took care

19:22.437 --> 19:24.024
of any assets he had left,

19:24.059 --> 19:28.408
but there were a few items
he wanted you to have.

19:33.102 --> 19:36.347
That's 9 grand the IRS
didn't know about.

19:38.729 --> 19:40.317
-Well, he never did cease
to amaze me

19:40.351 --> 19:44.666
how he could
turn a nickel into $5.

19:44.700 --> 19:46.530
-Gave me his Winchester rifle.

19:46.564 --> 19:49.740
Said it wouldn't fit in the box.

19:49.774 --> 19:51.707
I'll give you a minute.

19:53.640 --> 20:03.202
♪♪

20:03.236 --> 20:12.521
♪♪

20:12.556 --> 20:22.082
♪♪

20:22.117 --> 20:31.230
♪♪

20:31.264 --> 20:32.748
There is something else, Joe.

20:32.783 --> 20:36.235
The nursing home
forwarded his mail to me.

20:36.269 --> 20:37.822
Didn't know what you wanted me
to do with this.

20:37.857 --> 20:41.274
It's from Christopher.

20:41.309 --> 20:44.139
It's addressed to your father,
but I think it's meant for you.

20:45.036 --> 20:47.763
-♪ Every morning

20:47.798 --> 20:49.834
♪ When I wake

20:49.869 --> 20:52.009
♪ I pinch myself

20:52.043 --> 20:54.287
♪ Do a double take

20:54.322 --> 20:58.257
♪ I never dreamed of a day
like this ♪

20:58.291 --> 21:02.916
♪ Stuck on repeat
like a stolen kiss ♪

21:02.951 --> 21:05.091
♪ So far away

21:05.125 --> 21:07.266
♪ A year and a day

21:07.300 --> 21:11.649
♪ I'm counting the hours
till I see your face ♪

21:11.684 --> 21:13.927
♪ So far away

21:13.962 --> 21:15.826
♪ A year and a day

21:15.860 --> 21:21.487
♪ I can't wait to tell you
how I feel about you ♪

21:21.521 --> 21:23.661
-♪ I can't wait

21:23.696 --> 21:26.837
♪ I can't wait

21:26.871 --> 21:30.427
-♪ How I feel about you

21:30.461 --> 21:32.360
-♪ I can't wait

21:32.394 --> 21:35.604
♪ I can't wait

21:35.639 --> 21:38.814
-♪ How I feel about you

21:41.058 --> 21:43.405
[ Vehicle approaches,
horn honks ]

21:55.659 --> 21:58.351
[ Brakes squeal ]

22:01.389 --> 22:03.391
♪ Every morning

22:03.425 --> 22:05.531
♪ When I wake

22:05.565 --> 22:07.671
♪ I pinch myself

22:07.705 --> 22:10.156
♪ Do a double take

22:10.190 --> 22:14.091
-So, uh, you're not, like,
on vacation or anything?

22:14.125 --> 22:15.161
-♪ Stuck on repeat

22:15.195 --> 22:16.542
-You actually live in here?

22:16.576 --> 22:17.991
-♪ Like a stolen kiss

22:18.026 --> 22:20.649
-That's right.
-♪ So far away

22:20.684 --> 22:23.376
♪ A year and a day

22:23.411 --> 22:26.828
♪ I'm counting the hours
till I see your face ♪

22:26.862 --> 22:29.175
-Who are they?
-♪ So far away

22:29.209 --> 22:30.728
-Uh, sit back and mind
your own business

22:30.763 --> 22:32.730
before you make me
have an accident.

22:32.765 --> 22:33.869
-Oh, I'm just messing.

22:33.904 --> 22:35.388
-♪ How I feel about you

22:35.423 --> 22:38.218
-I got you.
Well, where are they?

22:38.253 --> 22:42.568
♪♪

22:42.602 --> 22:46.019
-♪ How I feel about you

22:46.054 --> 22:47.538
-Well, what have we here?

22:51.128 --> 22:53.717
-♪ How I feel about you

22:53.751 --> 22:56.375
[ Engine shuts off ]

22:56.409 --> 22:57.755
-We stopping?

22:57.790 --> 23:00.206
-Yeah, I got to make a living.

23:00.240 --> 23:01.621
-Hurry up.
It's hot in here.

23:01.656 --> 23:04.452
-Well, it was a lot hotter
on that road, wasn't it?

23:06.074 --> 23:08.317
[ Door opens ]

23:08.352 --> 23:09.733
-Could have
walked there faster.

23:09.767 --> 23:11.251
[ Door closes ]

23:15.186 --> 23:17.948
-What seems to be the problem?
-How you doing?

23:17.982 --> 23:19.432
Are you with, uh,
roadside assistance?

23:19.467 --> 23:21.710
-Uh, no. No, I'm not.
I just kind of do freelance.

23:21.745 --> 23:24.748
I might be able to get you
on the road a lot sooner.

23:24.782 --> 23:26.059
-Okay, good, good.

23:26.094 --> 23:27.613
Well, how much do you,
uh, you cost?

23:27.647 --> 23:31.548
-Well, I can guarantee you
I charge a lot less than...

23:31.582 --> 23:34.171
-Um, we were, like,
a couple miles down,

23:34.205 --> 23:36.000
and it started, uh...

23:36.035 --> 23:38.900
[ Conversation continues ]

23:38.934 --> 23:48.910
♪♪

23:48.944 --> 23:58.920
♪♪

23:58.954 --> 24:08.930
♪♪

24:08.964 --> 24:18.940
♪♪

24:18.974 --> 24:24.014
♪♪

24:46.554 --> 24:48.003
-Alright.
Cut the act, slick.

24:48.038 --> 24:49.902
I know you're not sleeping.

24:49.936 --> 24:52.352
-I was trying to.

24:56.011 --> 24:59.498
-Is everything in there?

24:59.532 --> 25:01.223
-Yeah, you know, of --
of course.

25:01.258 --> 25:03.916
I didn't take nothing, you know.
Just dropped my pencil.

25:03.950 --> 25:06.056
-Oh, yeah, where's your pencil?

25:09.542 --> 25:10.888
-You know what would
make more money?

25:10.923 --> 25:12.441
-Yeah, I saw you work
your marks

25:12.476 --> 25:13.719
in the pool hall, remember?

25:13.753 --> 25:16.031
-He was trying to get over
on me first.

25:16.066 --> 25:18.655
-Oh, and that's all
that matters, right?

25:18.689 --> 25:22.210
-Cal teaches me plenty.
-Yeah, it shows.

25:37.397 --> 25:40.090
Come on.
You're not staying in here.

25:58.936 --> 26:07.635
♪♪

26:07.669 --> 26:09.429
-Hey.

26:09.464 --> 26:10.707
Here.

26:10.741 --> 26:20.130
♪♪

26:20.164 --> 26:29.588
♪♪

26:29.622 --> 26:31.762
-Stop scribbling
on all my crap.

26:31.797 --> 26:40.771
♪♪

26:40.806 --> 26:49.815
♪♪

26:49.849 --> 26:58.824
♪♪

26:58.858 --> 27:07.867
♪♪

27:07.902 --> 27:16.876
♪♪

27:16.911 --> 27:18.567
-Why we stopping?

27:18.602 --> 27:26.645
♪♪

27:26.679 --> 27:34.687
♪♪

27:34.722 --> 27:42.799
♪♪

27:42.833 --> 27:44.076
-Now, you just stay put.

27:44.110 --> 27:46.734
I don't want you going anywhere.

27:46.768 --> 27:49.702
-If the air works.

27:49.737 --> 27:51.428
-Why wouldn't it?

27:55.259 --> 27:56.813
Now, don't touch anything.

27:56.847 --> 27:59.160
If you do, I'm gonna break
one of your skinny fingers.

27:59.194 --> 28:02.370
[ Rain falling ]

28:20.906 --> 28:23.322
[ Paper rustling ]

28:30.812 --> 28:33.021
-Joe.

28:33.056 --> 28:35.575
What in the name of God
are you doing here?

28:41.789 --> 28:45.240
-You've, uh, you've kept the
place looking real nice, Maggie.

28:45.275 --> 28:47.726
-Law says you can't be here.
-I know.

28:49.348 --> 28:51.315
I know, I --

28:51.350 --> 28:55.285
I, uh, you know,
I don't want any trouble.

28:56.907 --> 29:02.119
I just, um, I just wanted
to tell Christopher

29:02.154 --> 29:04.363
that his granddaddy passed away.

29:07.815 --> 29:09.886
-I'm sorry about that.
I'll let him know.

29:09.920 --> 29:12.336
-And would you give this
to him, please?

29:14.131 --> 29:15.926
-Chris isn't here.

29:15.961 --> 29:18.826
-Yes, I know he's moved on!
-Yes.

29:20.862 --> 29:23.727
-Who's there, Maggie?

29:25.142 --> 29:27.627
-Nobody.
I'll be right in.

29:29.802 --> 29:30.803
-Mm.

29:32.736 --> 29:35.187
-You just stay away from him.
It's the least you could do.

29:35.221 --> 29:38.949
[ Door closes ]

29:40.054 --> 29:42.815
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:42.850 --> 29:47.647
♪♪

29:47.682 --> 29:50.823
-Why'd the woman snub you
like that?

29:50.858 --> 29:53.792
I mean, personally, I --
I think it's kind of whacked.

29:53.826 --> 29:57.554
Why can't you give
your kid a gift?

29:57.588 --> 30:00.695
-You know the nice thing
about a personal life?

30:02.973 --> 30:08.013
It's personal.
-Hey, man, I'm on your side.

30:10.084 --> 30:11.810
-There are no sides.

30:13.881 --> 30:16.469
-Hmm, didn't like your
breakfast, honey?

30:16.504 --> 30:20.335
-Well, uh, he's having
some lady problems.

30:20.370 --> 30:23.580
Lost his appetite.

30:23.614 --> 30:25.340
-Everything was fine.

30:25.375 --> 30:27.066
Just the check, please.

30:32.382 --> 30:33.832
-Hey, uh, you know,

30:33.866 --> 30:35.868
I think I figured out
the problem with your kid.

30:35.903 --> 30:38.491
-Yeah, well,
I don't remember asking.

30:38.526 --> 30:39.665
-Just show up to the wedding
and give him

30:39.699 --> 30:41.322
the money in person.

30:41.356 --> 30:44.325
I mean, she can't stop
you then, right?

30:44.359 --> 30:46.085
-It's more complicated
than that.

30:46.120 --> 30:48.501
-Then, stop complicating it.

30:48.536 --> 30:49.917
What day is it?

30:49.951 --> 30:52.505
Sunday?

30:52.540 --> 30:55.543
Well, you know
I saw the invitation.

31:02.930 --> 31:06.243
We're still going to Fatty's,
right?

31:06.278 --> 31:16.253
♪♪

31:16.288 --> 31:21.776
♪♪

31:21.810 --> 31:26.885
♪♪

31:26.919 --> 31:28.610
-Hell, if he ain't
pissing people off,

31:28.645 --> 31:30.060
he's ripping them off.

31:30.095 --> 31:32.373
You know them chains and watches
he sells ain't real?

31:32.407 --> 31:33.892
-You know, I'm glad you won't
let him play in here.

31:33.926 --> 31:35.548
-He's more trouble
than he's worth.

31:35.583 --> 31:37.550
-This place is skanky anyway.
-Okay, enough.

31:37.585 --> 31:41.658
-Well, the apple don't fall too
far from the tree, does it?

31:41.692 --> 31:43.384
I can't imagine why
your daddy ain't home.

31:43.418 --> 31:44.557
-Fuck you, fat man.
-Okay.

31:44.592 --> 31:45.973
-[ Yells indistinctly ]

31:49.252 --> 31:50.943
-You know, it might be
in your best interest

31:50.978 --> 31:52.738
to keep your mouth shut
once in a while.

31:52.772 --> 31:55.603
-You know, Cal's talented,
and that makes people jealous.

31:55.637 --> 31:57.087
-Yeah, he may be talented,

31:57.122 --> 31:58.847
but the truth of the matter
is that your dad --

31:58.882 --> 32:00.435
-What would you know
about my dad?

32:00.470 --> 32:02.748
You live in a camper with a dog.

32:02.782 --> 32:04.853
-And what does that make me?

32:04.888 --> 32:07.615
-Someone whose own family
don't want him around.

32:28.015 --> 32:31.087
-You're Cal McCarthy's kid,
right?

32:31.121 --> 32:32.467
-Yeah, yeah.

32:32.502 --> 32:34.021
You were at the house, right?

32:34.055 --> 32:35.712
-Uh-huh.

32:35.746 --> 32:38.611
Where is he?
-I don't know.

32:38.646 --> 32:39.854
-Come look for him with us?

32:39.888 --> 32:43.340
-Dallas, we should probably
be going.

32:43.375 --> 32:45.273
-Hold on, cowboy.

32:45.308 --> 32:47.482
The three of us are talking.

32:47.517 --> 32:49.450
-I don't want to go anywhere
with you.

32:49.484 --> 32:54.110
-Hey, hear that?
The boy don't want to go.

32:54.144 --> 32:57.009
Maybe you would like to stay and
hang out with us for a spell.

32:57.044 --> 32:59.736
Do you know, your daddy and me,
we go way back.

32:59.770 --> 33:02.635
-Yeah, well, that's all well
and good, but, uh,

33:02.670 --> 33:04.568
the boy is in my charge,
so if you don't mind.

33:04.603 --> 33:06.329
-Oh, we mind.

33:06.363 --> 33:09.366
-Might be best if you hop back
in your time machine

33:09.401 --> 33:11.817
and made yourself scarce.

33:11.851 --> 33:13.129
-That's just not
gonna happen.

33:13.163 --> 33:14.647
-That's not a request.

33:14.682 --> 33:15.924
-You know what?
I -- I changed my mind.

33:15.959 --> 33:17.581
I'm -- I'm gonna go.
-No, kid.

33:17.616 --> 33:18.824
-You want my advice?

33:18.858 --> 33:20.170
Save yourself
a little bit of pain

33:20.205 --> 33:22.034
and suffering and walk away.

33:24.381 --> 33:26.073
-Alright, old man.

33:29.559 --> 33:32.527
-Dallas, you get
in the RV right now.

33:32.562 --> 33:34.529
-Come on.

33:36.359 --> 33:39.051
Aah! God.
[ Groans ]

33:47.197 --> 33:53.583
♪♪

33:53.617 --> 33:56.551
-It's a good thing
you aren't gonna live

33:56.586 --> 33:58.795
long enough to reproduce.

34:01.073 --> 34:02.626
Oh, what?
A cat's got your tongue now?

34:02.661 --> 34:04.180
-Okay, that was stupid.

34:04.214 --> 34:06.113
-No, that was 85 miles
past stupid.

34:06.147 --> 34:08.839
-Yeah, I'm sorry. Okay?
Can you just get off my back?

34:10.600 --> 34:12.533
-I got a better idea.

34:12.567 --> 34:14.052
I'm gonna get you
off my back.

34:14.085 --> 34:15.293
[ Dog barking ]

34:15.329 --> 34:16.744
Stay, girl!

34:16.777 --> 34:19.297
-Where we going?
-We're not going anywhere.

34:19.333 --> 34:20.713
You're going home.

34:20.748 --> 34:22.543
You're gonna call someone
to come get you.

34:22.577 --> 34:25.891
-I already told you.
-I don't care.

34:25.925 --> 34:28.273
Call anyone.
-What?

34:28.306 --> 34:30.206
I'm not your fricking problem,
okay?

34:30.239 --> 34:33.761
Just leave me alone.
You don't understand.

34:33.795 --> 34:35.280
I know where he's headed.

34:35.313 --> 34:37.315
Look, listen, there's a poster
back at Fatty's, okay?

34:37.351 --> 34:39.422
There's a big pool tournament
this weekend in New Orleans,

34:39.456 --> 34:40.664
and he's gonna be there.

34:40.699 --> 34:43.011
-That couldn't matter
less to me.

34:43.045 --> 34:44.909
Either you start dialing
or I'm gonna call a cop.

34:44.944 --> 34:46.739
This is your choice.

34:46.774 --> 34:49.501
-You know what? Fine.
Go ahead.

34:49.534 --> 34:52.676
Then I'll never see him again.

34:52.710 --> 34:54.299
I fricking lied, okay?

34:54.333 --> 34:56.094
He's not coming back for me.

34:56.128 --> 35:03.653
♪♪

35:03.687 --> 35:11.488
♪♪

35:11.523 --> 35:13.180
-You coming?!

35:13.214 --> 35:22.534
♪♪

35:22.568 --> 35:32.164
♪♪

35:32.199 --> 35:39.137
♪♪

35:39.171 --> 35:41.622
-I screwed up
on the hands a bit.

35:41.656 --> 35:43.210
-Well, that's not half bad.

35:43.244 --> 35:46.627
I think you ought to do
something with that.

35:46.661 --> 35:49.181
-With what?
-That.

35:49.216 --> 35:51.632
-You mean like a job
or something?

35:51.666 --> 35:53.565
-Yeah, like a job or something.

35:53.599 --> 35:54.807
-Who's gonna pay me
to do this?

35:54.842 --> 35:58.466
-A lot of people.

35:58.501 --> 36:02.815
-Kind of just figured
I would play pool.

36:02.850 --> 36:05.301
-Yeah, well, I'm sure Cal
will be proud of you

36:05.335 --> 36:06.785
no matter what you do.

36:11.099 --> 36:13.688
-Alright.
Come on, Story, go get it.

36:13.723 --> 36:15.345
Bring it here.

36:15.380 --> 36:24.665
♪♪

36:24.699 --> 36:33.777
♪♪

36:33.812 --> 36:38.713
-You're the first person she's
let throw a ball besides me.

36:38.748 --> 36:41.337
-Really?

36:41.371 --> 36:44.374
-Yeah, she must have guessed
you had a good arm.

36:44.409 --> 36:46.204
-My dad taught me.

36:46.238 --> 36:47.688
He was a pitcher in high school.

36:47.722 --> 36:50.242
-Is that right?

36:50.277 --> 36:53.970
-You know, um,
I actually played for a bit.

36:54.004 --> 36:56.524
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

36:56.559 --> 36:59.251
You know, my mom worked a lot
and my dad couldn't always

36:59.286 --> 37:01.874
get me to practice,
so had to quit.

37:01.909 --> 37:03.393
-Had to quit.

37:03.428 --> 37:05.913
Well, we couldn't get enough
of baseball in our house.

37:05.947 --> 37:09.296
Yeah, we...we ate it.
We drank it.

37:09.330 --> 37:12.368
We slept with it.

37:12.402 --> 37:14.887
Whenever there was a game on,
we'd go out on the porch

37:14.922 --> 37:17.476
and listen to the play-by-play
on the radio,

37:17.511 --> 37:22.895
ask each other about players'
stats, you know, and all.

37:22.930 --> 37:25.243
We could not stump my youngest.

37:25.277 --> 37:26.865
-What's his name?

37:31.525 --> 37:33.112
[ Dog barking ]

37:34.597 --> 37:37.082
-You got any favorite memories?

37:37.116 --> 37:41.293
-I mean, I don't know.
I got lots of them.

37:41.328 --> 37:43.847
-Any one of them
stick out in your mind?

37:48.438 --> 37:54.099
-Well, this one time when I was
about 7 or something,

37:54.133 --> 37:55.825
I remember my dad bought

37:55.859 --> 37:57.758
this really bitching
Triumph motorcycle,

37:57.792 --> 38:00.208
and we took a ride
out to the country,

38:00.243 --> 38:02.521
to one of his buddies' houses.

38:02.556 --> 38:05.421
You know, a whole bunch of guys
hanging out.

38:05.455 --> 38:07.319
They didn't mind me.

38:07.354 --> 38:10.218
They even let me play
a few hands of cards with them.

38:10.253 --> 38:13.774
I remember when it came time
to leave,

38:13.808 --> 38:15.154
my dad sat me in front of him

38:15.189 --> 38:18.813
and wrapped me up
in his big old leather jacket.

38:20.505 --> 38:22.852
I still remember
what it smelled like.

38:26.856 --> 38:28.961
Pretty stupid, huh?

38:28.996 --> 38:33.552
-No, no. That's --
that's not stupid at all.

38:33.587 --> 38:36.728
-You know, my dad's not
a bad person.

38:36.762 --> 38:38.799
-Yeah, well,
I'm not here to judge.

38:38.833 --> 38:48.326
♪♪

38:48.360 --> 38:57.542
♪♪

38:57.576 --> 39:06.827
♪♪

39:06.861 --> 39:16.354
♪♪

39:16.388 --> 39:18.597
[ Siren wailing ]

39:18.632 --> 39:20.392
[ Sighs in frustration ]

39:20.427 --> 39:23.775
Ugh.

39:23.809 --> 39:30.782
♪♪

39:30.816 --> 39:37.547
♪♪

39:37.582 --> 39:39.411
-Do you know you have
a taillight out?

39:39.446 --> 39:41.517
-Uh, yes, I do.
I do apologize.

39:41.551 --> 39:44.140
-License, registration,
proof of insurance.

39:44.174 --> 39:46.591
[ Police radio chatter ]

39:52.251 --> 39:55.462
-Okay, Houdini,
you can come out now.

39:55.496 --> 39:58.568
This might be the time
for you to come clean.

40:00.605 --> 40:01.778
-Not really.

40:01.813 --> 40:03.228
-Well, let me rephrase
that then.

40:03.262 --> 40:05.955
This is the time that you are
gonna come clean.

40:05.989 --> 40:07.439
-Okay, fine, I'll tell you
when she leaves.

40:07.474 --> 40:08.820
-No, you're gonna
tell me now

40:08.854 --> 40:09.959
or you're gonna be
leaving with her.

40:09.993 --> 40:11.581
-Okay, okay.
Fine, fine.

40:14.860 --> 40:17.415
This cop might be
looking for me.

40:17.449 --> 40:19.658
-For any particular reason?

40:19.693 --> 40:21.729
-Because my mom has probably
got half of Louisiana

40:21.764 --> 40:23.179
out hunting for me by now.

40:23.213 --> 40:26.976
-Hmm, and that would be
your dead mom?

40:28.598 --> 40:29.944
-You wouldn't have helped me
find him

40:29.979 --> 40:31.429
if I told you the truth.

40:31.463 --> 40:34.362
-She know where you are
and what you are doing?

40:37.365 --> 40:40.161
-No.

40:40.196 --> 40:42.094
So you gonna turn me in?

40:42.129 --> 40:43.820
-I don't know yet.

40:43.855 --> 40:45.615
The day's not over.

40:47.548 --> 40:50.448
I know there's one thing
you're gonna do for me.

40:52.795 --> 40:55.073
[ Cellphone ringing ]

40:57.972 --> 40:59.974
-Hello?
-Mom?

41:00.009 --> 41:02.183
-Dallas.
What are you doing, baby?

41:02.218 --> 41:03.495
Are you okay?

41:03.530 --> 41:05.463
-Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.
I'm with a friend.

41:05.497 --> 41:06.947
-What friend?

41:06.981 --> 41:09.984
-Doesn't matter.
He's taking me to Dad.

41:10.019 --> 41:12.297
-No, no.
Tell me where you are.

41:12.331 --> 41:14.402
I'll come get you.
-Not yet.

41:14.437 --> 41:16.301
Mom, I'm gonna bring him back.
-What?

41:16.335 --> 41:19.097
-I'm gonna bring Dad home.
-What?

41:21.720 --> 41:23.791
Dally, honey,

41:23.826 --> 41:26.656
this ain't got nothing
to do with you, okay?

41:29.176 --> 41:30.522
-I'll be home in a day or two.

41:30.557 --> 41:32.006
-A day --

41:32.041 --> 41:34.630
Don't do this to me.

41:34.664 --> 41:37.874
Dallas, please, don't.

41:37.909 --> 41:40.877
Dallas.
-I -- I got to go.

41:40.912 --> 41:42.672
-Dallas.

41:49.023 --> 41:52.026
-You feel better now?

41:52.061 --> 41:53.511
-It's overrated.

42:07.386 --> 42:09.872
-What are these for?

42:09.906 --> 42:11.943
-You earned those.

42:11.977 --> 42:13.392
You did right by your mama.

42:13.427 --> 42:15.256
Besides, you don't want to smell
like old cheese

42:15.291 --> 42:16.913
when you meet with your father.

42:16.948 --> 42:22.298
♪♪

42:22.332 --> 42:24.852
-♪ We tried real hard

42:24.887 --> 42:27.717
♪ Only the Lord knows why

42:27.752 --> 42:29.754
♪ I never did see

42:29.788 --> 42:31.894
♪ What I did wrong

42:31.928 --> 42:33.620
-Oh, Ricky.
Did you hear that?

42:33.654 --> 42:37.693
I think that is the sound of you
going to the poor house.

42:37.727 --> 42:40.109
-I bet you're gonna go there
before I do.

42:41.593 --> 42:43.733
-Oh, shit.
That's alright.

42:43.768 --> 42:45.321
I'm gonna be over here
with my little private

42:45.355 --> 42:48.738
cheering section while you clear
the table for me.

42:49.912 --> 42:51.430
-Hey, Dad.

42:52.984 --> 42:55.331
Miss me?

42:55.365 --> 42:58.334
-Dallas, what are you
doing here?

42:58.368 --> 43:00.474
-Came to find you.

43:00.508 --> 43:03.235
-Uh, is your mama here?

43:03.270 --> 43:07.136
-No, and good thing she ain't.

43:07.170 --> 43:09.587
She the reason you left?

43:09.621 --> 43:10.967
-No, hell, no.

43:11.002 --> 43:13.314
-I'm not an idiot.

43:13.349 --> 43:15.627
-No, no, some fellow is
bothering her, so, you know,

43:15.662 --> 43:17.836
I was just pretending
to be her boyfriend is all.

43:17.871 --> 43:20.356
Don't bust my balls.

43:20.390 --> 43:22.945
-That's all it was?

43:22.979 --> 43:24.705
-'Course that's all it was.

43:26.776 --> 43:29.123
-Then why did you leave?

43:29.158 --> 43:31.160
-Well, Dallas, you know, it...

43:34.301 --> 43:37.166
Hey, how did you
get here anyway?

43:40.479 --> 43:43.551
-My friend Joe Haley
gave me a ride.

43:43.586 --> 43:49.178
♪♪

43:49.212 --> 43:51.145
-That so?

43:54.355 --> 43:57.186
-Joe Haley.

43:57.220 --> 43:58.670
-Hey, Dallas, why don't you,

43:58.705 --> 44:01.121
uh, why don't you go get us
a couple of drinks?

44:01.155 --> 44:03.399
-Okay.
Want anything?

44:03.433 --> 44:05.332
-Nope, no, thanks.

44:07.161 --> 44:09.819
-I suppose you know what's
going through my head right now,

44:09.854 --> 44:12.995
so why don't you tell me
how a grown man knows

44:13.029 --> 44:16.308
my 14-year-old boy?

44:16.343 --> 44:17.793
-He was on the side
of the road.

44:17.827 --> 44:22.142
His bike had broke down,
and I just offered him a ride.

44:22.176 --> 44:24.144
He said he was looking
for his dad.

44:24.178 --> 44:27.319
-[ Chuckles ]

44:27.354 --> 44:30.633
Well, you found me.

44:34.879 --> 44:36.156
Where you from?

44:36.190 --> 44:39.159
-Uh, mostly here.
Yourself?

44:39.193 --> 44:41.092
-Here and there, I guess.

44:41.126 --> 44:43.059
-Mm. You guess, yeah.

44:43.094 --> 44:45.683
-What do you mean by that?

44:45.717 --> 44:47.719
-Uh, nothing.

44:47.754 --> 44:49.790
No, really, not--
nothing at all.

44:53.380 --> 44:56.107
-You know, Joe, uh,

44:56.141 --> 45:00.594
there ain't no road map
to being a daddy, you know?

45:00.628 --> 45:03.873
We just do the best we can.

45:03.908 --> 45:06.704
-Yeah, you got that right.

45:06.738 --> 45:08.257
-Thank you, boy.

45:12.571 --> 45:15.195
-Well, it was nice
talking to you.

45:15.229 --> 45:17.542
-Yeah.
-Um, I-I'm gonna go.

45:17.576 --> 45:18.750
-Come on, Joe. Come on.

45:18.785 --> 45:20.131
You don't want to hang
for a little?

45:20.165 --> 45:22.754
-No.

45:22.789 --> 45:24.791
-Hey, Joe.

45:24.825 --> 45:26.585
I just...

45:26.620 --> 45:28.242
I wanted to say thank you.

45:28.277 --> 45:30.762
-Uh, you bet.

45:30.797 --> 45:35.663
I'll put your backpack and
your bike in your daddy's truck.

45:39.253 --> 45:41.462
-Okay.

45:42.947 --> 45:46.260
Oh, hey, and Joe,
don't worry about the wedding.

45:46.295 --> 45:53.233
♪♪

45:53.267 --> 45:56.236
-Your buddy is leaving, huh?

45:56.270 --> 45:58.065
-Yeah.

45:58.100 --> 45:59.791
-I'm sorry about that.

46:03.691 --> 46:05.072
How about we do what we do

46:05.107 --> 46:07.419
and get down
to some serious matters, okay?

46:07.454 --> 46:10.319
We've got some fish to fry.

46:10.353 --> 46:12.079
Alright, folks.

46:12.114 --> 46:17.084
I've got 50 bucks says this boy
can beat anybody in this room.

46:17.119 --> 46:22.814
♪♪

46:22.849 --> 46:28.371
♪♪

46:28.406 --> 46:31.271
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

46:31.305 --> 46:40.936
♪♪

46:40.970 --> 46:43.939
-$20, $40, $60, $80, $81.

46:43.973 --> 46:45.837
Easy money, huh?

46:45.872 --> 46:49.737
That sure as hell beats 9-5,
barely alive.

46:53.189 --> 46:54.673
-Why do you do it?

46:58.263 --> 46:59.989
-Why do I do it?

47:01.991 --> 47:05.512
It's in my blood, just like
it was in your grandpa Gus'

47:05.546 --> 47:08.515
and just like it's in yours.

47:18.456 --> 47:20.458
You're making me
lose count here.

47:26.257 --> 47:28.259
Alright.

47:28.293 --> 47:30.019
Why you so moody?

47:32.263 --> 47:34.679
-Look, you just made
some money.

47:34.713 --> 47:36.232
Can we just go home now?

47:36.267 --> 47:38.441
-Dallas, tournament
is tomorrow.

47:38.476 --> 47:41.582
I didn't come all this way
not to play.

47:41.617 --> 47:44.413
-Fine, after the tournament.

47:44.447 --> 47:45.690
-We'll talk about it later.

47:45.724 --> 47:47.416
-No, why can't we
talk about it now?

47:47.450 --> 47:49.383
-Stop riding me, boy.

47:55.907 --> 47:57.564
Okay.

47:59.048 --> 48:01.706
Why don't you take this,
go get us a couple of sodas?

48:01.740 --> 48:02.914
I'm gonna take a shower.

48:02.949 --> 48:05.227
Afterwards, we'll go
grab a burger.

48:05.261 --> 48:06.953
Does that sound alright?

48:16.824 --> 48:18.274
Dallas.

48:18.309 --> 48:20.414
You okay?

48:20.449 --> 48:21.657
It's okay.
It's alright.

48:21.691 --> 48:23.624
I know these guys.

48:23.659 --> 48:27.145
-Cal, why did you make us
chase you

48:27.180 --> 48:30.079
halfway across the state?

48:30.114 --> 48:33.393
-It's $1,000.

48:33.427 --> 48:36.085
$1,000. Take it.

48:36.120 --> 48:37.431
-You're five short,
son of a bitch.

48:37.466 --> 48:40.227
-No!
Please don't hurt him.

48:40.262 --> 48:41.953
Don't do it.
Dad.

48:41.988 --> 48:45.232
What are you doing?
No, wait, please.

48:45.267 --> 48:48.339
-How am I supposed to pay
you back if I can't play?

48:48.373 --> 48:49.788
-No, wait, please.

48:49.823 --> 48:51.549
I -- I -- I know where
we can get the money.

48:54.138 --> 48:57.796
Dad, just promise me
you'll come home?

48:57.831 --> 49:02.456
♪♪

49:02.491 --> 49:04.424
-Okay.

49:04.458 --> 49:11.603
♪♪

49:11.638 --> 49:13.640
[ Vehicle doors close ]

49:16.746 --> 49:18.196
[ Dog barking ]

49:18.231 --> 49:20.440
-There's a dog.

49:20.474 --> 49:22.200
-Just get the box.
I'll distract it.

49:22.235 --> 49:24.720
Just get the box.
Go.

49:24.754 --> 49:27.274
[ Smooching ] Hey.

49:27.309 --> 49:28.448
Hey.

49:28.482 --> 49:34.385
♪♪

49:34.419 --> 49:36.663
-[ Barking continues ]
-Shh.

49:40.322 --> 49:42.910
-Get out of here!
-Oh!

49:42.945 --> 49:44.360
[ Grunts ]

49:44.395 --> 49:48.330
[ Barking continues ]

49:48.364 --> 49:51.885
[ Groans ]

49:51.919 --> 49:54.025
-Ah!

49:54.060 --> 50:00.204
♪♪

50:00.238 --> 50:06.382
♪♪

50:06.417 --> 50:08.177
-Get the money.

50:08.212 --> 50:10.214
[ Barking continues ]

50:10.248 --> 50:15.495
♪♪

