[ Vehicle doors close ]

50:17.635 --> 50:20.155
[ Engine starts ]

50:20.189 --> 50:23.192
-[ Groans ]

50:23.227 --> 50:33.202
♪♪

50:33.237 --> 50:38.897
♪♪

50:38.932 --> 50:44.351
♪♪

50:44.386 --> 50:48.045
-Hey, kiddo.

50:48.079 --> 50:49.770
Are you okay?

50:51.910 --> 50:54.534
-I just want to go home.

50:54.568 --> 50:56.260
-Yeah.

51:01.817 --> 51:03.819
I'm sorry about your friend.

51:03.853 --> 51:06.822
You know, to be honest with you,

51:06.856 --> 51:09.859
I sometimes forget
you're just 14.

51:13.277 --> 51:16.556
I know you want to go home,
and I don't want you to worry,

51:16.590 --> 51:20.284
so first thing in the morning,
we're gonna put you on a bus.

51:20.318 --> 51:22.596
Okay?

51:22.631 --> 51:24.771
-But you said you were
coming with me.

51:28.637 --> 51:31.295
-I'm not, Dallas.

51:31.329 --> 51:33.055
-You promised.

51:36.058 --> 51:37.266
-I know.

51:38.888 --> 51:41.995
[ Sighs ]
I know I did.

51:44.722 --> 51:47.414
Listen...

51:47.449 --> 51:48.933
I am not good...

51:48.967 --> 51:52.488
As a matter of fact, I am
horrible at playing pretend,

51:52.523 --> 51:55.526
and I've been doing it too long,

51:55.560 --> 51:56.803
and it's not fair to your mama,

51:56.837 --> 51:59.288
and it's certainly
not fair to you.

52:02.533 --> 52:06.468
The fact of the matter is I --
I can't do it anymore.

52:06.502 --> 52:08.055
-But --

52:08.090 --> 52:11.990
-Just hear me out, please.

52:13.992 --> 52:17.203
See, me, I am who I am.

52:17.237 --> 52:18.963
[ Chuckles ]

52:18.997 --> 52:20.620
And I'm gonna have to live
with that forever,

52:20.654 --> 52:24.175
but that does not mean that I
have to put you through it, too.

52:26.902 --> 52:29.076
I mean, look at us, Dallas.

52:29.111 --> 52:30.388
I'm supposed to be your daddy,

52:30.423 --> 52:35.221
and you're the one
that's taking care of me.

52:38.258 --> 52:42.814
Look, the best thing I can do
for everyone

52:42.849 --> 52:45.955
is to not go back.

52:48.406 --> 52:49.649
-But mom needs you.

52:49.683 --> 52:52.099
-No. [ Chuckles ]

52:52.134 --> 52:54.826
No, your mama doesn't need me.

52:54.861 --> 52:57.035
The only one mama needs is you.

53:00.073 --> 53:02.040
-You lie.

53:02.075 --> 53:05.527
You lie about everything.
-Yeah.

53:05.561 --> 53:08.046
Yeah, I know.

53:08.081 --> 53:11.843
The thing is, though, I'm not
lying about this,

53:11.878 --> 53:14.605
and some day you're going
to realize very soon

53:14.639 --> 53:18.574
that I was really never there.

53:18.609 --> 53:24.373
♪♪

53:24.408 --> 53:30.207
♪♪

53:30.241 --> 53:31.794
[ Sniffling ]

53:31.829 --> 53:41.804
♪♪

53:41.839 --> 53:51.814
♪♪

53:51.849 --> 54:01.824
♪♪

54:01.859 --> 54:11.834
♪♪

54:11.869 --> 54:21.844
♪♪

54:21.879 --> 54:31.854
♪♪

54:31.889 --> 54:41.864
♪♪

54:41.899 --> 54:49.009
♪♪

54:49.044 --> 54:51.184
-Get out of here, kid.
-Joe, I...

54:51.218 --> 54:53.151
-You're a little prick.
-I...

54:56.154 --> 54:59.088
-What, what, what?
You're sorry, right?

55:01.470 --> 55:03.886
-I didn't have a choice.

55:03.921 --> 55:06.372
-You always have a choice.

55:07.994 --> 55:10.307
-They were gonna cut off
my dad's finger.

55:12.101 --> 55:16.451
-Well, none of that matters
anymore.

55:16.485 --> 55:20.696
-Joe, wh-what can I do?
I'll do anything.

55:20.731 --> 55:22.733
-You can leave.

55:22.767 --> 55:29.636
♪♪

55:29.671 --> 55:36.263
♪♪

55:36.298 --> 55:37.679
-Come on, girl.
You got to eat.

55:37.713 --> 55:39.853
Come on, Story.

55:44.410 --> 55:46.101
[ Sighs ]

55:50.588 --> 55:52.832
[ Birds chirping ]

55:52.866 --> 55:56.525
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

56:36.082 --> 56:40.051
♪♪

56:40.086 --> 56:42.571
[ Indistinct conversations ]

56:46.506 --> 56:47.645
-Can I help you?

56:47.680 --> 56:49.129
-I want to sign up.

56:52.478 --> 56:53.996
-Dallas?

56:54.031 --> 57:00.658
♪♪

57:00.693 --> 57:04.006
-I'm not here for you.

57:04.041 --> 57:07.285
I'm here to beat you.

57:07.320 --> 57:08.839
-Ladies and gentlemen,

57:08.873 --> 57:13.119
welcome to the one and only
Lacy's Cue 9-Ball Open.

57:13.153 --> 57:14.327
[ Cheers and applause ]

57:14.361 --> 57:16.743
Alright.
Let's hear it.

57:16.778 --> 57:18.573
Let's get this party started.

57:18.607 --> 57:28.583
♪♪

57:28.617 --> 57:38.593
♪♪

57:38.627 --> 57:48.603
♪♪

57:48.637 --> 57:53.677
♪♪

57:53.711 --> 57:55.472
[ Applause ]

57:55.506 --> 57:57.370
-Somebody should have
warned me.

57:57.404 --> 58:07.380
♪♪

58:07.414 --> 58:17.390
♪♪

58:17.424 --> 58:23.016
♪♪

58:23.051 --> 58:25.156
[ Crowd groans ]

58:25.191 --> 58:33.820
♪♪

58:33.855 --> 58:35.857
[ Applause ]

58:35.891 --> 58:39.861
♪♪

58:39.895 --> 58:43.105
-Tell you what,
you're impressing me today.

58:44.451 --> 58:46.661
I did notice you were
a little tight on the breaks,

58:46.695 --> 58:50.043
maybe just loosen up
that backstroke a little bit.

58:50.078 --> 58:56.049
♪♪

58:56.084 --> 58:57.948
Or just do it your own way.

58:57.982 --> 59:04.092
♪♪

59:04.126 --> 59:10.270
♪♪

59:10.305 --> 59:13.515
[ Cheers and applause ]

59:16.311 --> 59:19.452
-Dallas McCarthy.

59:19.486 --> 59:22.904
I tell you, folks, this boy
is only 14 years old.

59:22.938 --> 59:24.561
I don't know for sure,

59:24.595 --> 59:27.218
but I think we could be making
some history here tonight.

59:27.253 --> 59:29.393
Let's hear it for all
the players we've had

59:29.427 --> 59:30.636
